e since 1970  The Gillis Theater utilizes over 100 theatre grade lights  an advanced sound and projection system  a full size stage  balcony and orchestra levels  a professional sound proofing system to keep outside noises out  and a highly effective communications network for our technical crews  Other areas of the Center for Leadership and Ethics being used by the VMI Theatre Players include a Green Room  Rehearsal Hall  two dressing rooms  a theatre office  a box office  and a concessions stand  Adjacent to the Gillis Theatre is the ballroom and conference center named the Hall of Valor  For more information on the facilities contact the VMI Theatre   VMI Theatre Show Dates Tickets Directions Parking Leslie Gillis  29 Theater Additional Information CLE Home Gillis Theatre Past Productions Reservations Theatre Staff Joellen Bland Theatre Director P   540  464 7389 102 Marshall Hall Center for Leadership   Ethics Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA  24450 Email the VMI Theatre  CLE Home Gillis Theatre Past Productions Reservations Theatre Staff Joellen Bland Theatre Director P   540  464 7389 102 Marshall Hall Center for Leadership   Ethics Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA  24450 Email the VMI Theatre CLE Home Gillis Theatre Past Productions Reservations Theatre Staff CLE Home CLE Home Gillis Theatre Gillis Theatre Gillis Theatre Past Productions Past Productions Reservations Reservations Theatre Staff Theatre Staff Joellen Bland Theatre Director P   540  464 7389 102 Marshall Hall Center for Leadership   Ethics Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA  24450 Email the VMI Theatre Joellen Bland Theatre Director P   540  464 7389 102 Marshall Hall Center for Leadership   Ethics Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA  24450 Email the VMI Theatre Joellen Bland           Email the VMI Theatre Gillis Theatre After thirty nine years of performing at various venues  the VMI Theatre has a new home in a beautiful 500 seat theatre  and a long awaited dream